The paper deals with the problem of learning to rank from multiple sources, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). The proposed method involves the use of autoencoder-like networks, which are commonly used in deep learning (DL) and ML. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
